Virus specific qPCRs were carried out to quantify the amount of virus amplicons obtained for each virus using the 50 hexamer, RiboMinus™ and random priming protocols (Table 3
). Considering the Ct values, there appears to be no pattern to suggest that any of the three protocols are contributing to a higher sensitivity in amplifying viral nucleic acid extracted from tissues samples. The removal or exclusion of rRNA from virus positive tissues was also quantified by an 18S rRNA qPCR using cDNA, generated with the 50 hexamers, RiboMinus™ and random priming protocols, as template (Table 4
). The cDNAs generated with the 50 hexamers showed marginal effect whilst the RiboMinus™ protocol demonstrated a clear decrease in rRNA, compared to those cDNAs generated with random priming protocol.
